    },
    {
      "id": "WOCB5NfnHcmddm-MAdoqw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2958.6588040357183,
      "y": 3648.5050147324255,
      "width": 1018.9192504882812,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4R",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2080602224,
      "version": 457,
      "versionNonce": 326969456,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770729729593,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "here we can try scaling an unindexed db, but it will be terribly slow, here we have to use inverted index, \nwe will store the inverted index in an in memory cache like redis so the searching becomes very fast  \n\nWhen posts are created, we will break them inside the ingestion service and add it to the inverted index",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "here we can try scaling an unindexed db, but it will be terribly slow, here we have to use inverted index, \nwe will store the inverted index in an in memory cache like redis so the searching becomes very fast  \n\nWhen posts are created, we will break them inside the ingestion service and add it to the inverted index",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ynpw4d4rRVmK6wmPFVTHV",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1723.9853751576563,
      "y": 3476.494955837448,
      "width": 321.019775390625,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4S",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 478195344,
      "version": 380,
      "versionNonce": 421138032,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770731859355,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. durability concerns for redis\nstoring the inverted index\n\n2. post id list getting very long\nin the inverted index is a legit\nconcern\n\n3. are we replacing the previously\ndiscussed inverted index, with \nthese two new inverted indexes?\n\n4. Redis will keep the inverted\nindex in memory, its not acting\nas a cacheeeeeee\n \n5. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. durability concerns for redis\nstoring the inverted index\n\n2. post id list getting very long\nin the inverted index is a legit\nconcern\n\n3. are we replacing the previously\ndiscussed inverted index, with \nthese two new inverted indexes?\n\n4. Redis will keep the inverted\nindex in memory, its not acting\nas a cacheeeeeee\n \n5. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "plPEQbbcP_FFd-XCSVu63",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -3055.7442360500627,
      "y": 3888.0527654634675,
      "width": 1133.6591796875,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4T",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 732273776,
      "version": 465,
      "versionNonce": 21380208,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770730295787,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "getting search results sorted by recency or like counts makes me think of index on the timestamp or like count\n                                                        \n                                                                but\nthere's already a sequence existing, query -> inverted index -> fetch the list of postids from the inverted index list\n-> now to get it in a sorted manner is a new problem to be solved -> this is what the fundamentals need",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "getting search results sorted by recency or like counts makes me think of index on the timestamp or like count\n                                                        \n                                                                but\nthere's already a sequence existing, query -> inverted index -> fetch the list of postids from the inverted index list\n-> now to get it in a sorted manner is a new problem to be solved -> this is what the fundamentals need",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
